profile:
Susan founded happy pea in 2013 after a long career in the Investment Industry. When working through potential company names she was struck both by the perfect design of a pea pod that allows it to hold the peas, and nothing else, and the fact that no one can say “happy” without smiling. Susan knew that she’d often be helping clients deal with less than happy situations, so, happy pea was born. It still makes her smile.
 
You can expect:
 
Guidance and direction in making difficult decisions
Support and practical solutions
Discreet and non-judging atmosphere
About The Professional Organizer.
Susan Hammond is a Trained Professional Organizer, and a member of Professional Organizers in Canada. Along with earning a Certificate of Study in Understanding the Needs of the Aging Chronically Disorganized Client, she has received her Hoarding, CD and ADHD Specialist Certificate from the Institute for Challenging Organization.
 
She loves coaching overwhelmed clients to stop worrying about the forest and just deal with one tree at a time.
 
A two time Ironman finisher who still loves to swim, bike, and run, Susan brings energy, humour and focus to every project she takes on.
 
Susan is very involved in her association, Professional Organizers in Canada, serving as Chair on the Toronto Chapter Board.
name: Happy Pea

profile:
Ivanka is a Professional Organizer and Decluttering expert for homes, offices and schools - Specializing in Children's Spaces. 
   
Ivanka is a former Elementary School Teacher whose life was transformed when she began learning the many benefits of minimalism and organization!

 

Although she was always considered a tidy individual, after decluttering, and applying minimalism to her surroundings, it was as if the pieces of Ivanka's life puzzle all fell into place. Not only is her living space in order, she has a new found inner peace, and is able to recognize the things in her life that truly matter!

 

It is because of these life-altering improvements that Ivanka decided to become a full time Professional Organizer - to help others find that same inner peace in their daily lives!

​

Ivanka also put her Masters of Education, and child psychology knowledge to work in creating her own children’s organization program, "The Moose Method" - for homes and classrooms. This program is aimed to help children declutter their minds in order to prepare them for proper learning and development.

    
Ivanka not only shares the knowledge and skills of organizing but also helps her clients identify what he or she values in life, through the process of organizing and decluttering.

 

The Tidy Moose conducts private organizing sessions for both individual and group clients: Homes, offices, businesses, & schools. 

 

Ivanka coaches and supports the client(s) to completely organize their space, creating his or her ideal oasis, while being fully aware that organizing one’s space is a very personal issue.

 

What is a client’s ideal space? When considered at the deepest level, it translates into, “How does one want to live his or her life?” In understanding the true desires of the client, Ivanka is a partner in the process of achieving this ideal by using the several different methods catering to the client's needs, including her own Moose Method for Children, minimalism, and the KonMari Method of organization (under which she is fully certified).

 

Let's organize our lives one space at a time!
services:

specialities:
The Life-Changing Magic of Tidying Up by Marie Kondo, a best-seller which introduces the KonMari Method, has received international acclaim and has been featured in publications such as The New York Times, The Wall Street Journal, and The New Yorker. As of today, the book sold over 6 million copies, and is available in over 30 countries.

​

Kondo’s KonMari Method is attracting worldwide attention and is being implemented by readers, who are “kondoing,” or tidying up, their homes. People are drawn to the philosophy not only due to its effectiveness, but also because it places great importance on being mindful, introspective, and optimistic. Belongings are acknowledged for their service and thanked before being discarded, if they no longer spark joy.
name: The Tidy Moose
